args:
Tales of a dangerous fiend bring the prince
to Mount Archeole, where he meets Celliera,
a knight's armsmaster. She explains that
she, too, seeks the same massive beast,
and they decide to pursue it together.
The black mana thickens... I can see his\nimage dancing in its whorls.
Phraeganoth, the world-devourer...\nAt this rate, it's only a matter of time\nbefore he is reborn.
That abomination cannot be allowed\nto return. I must move quickly...
I'd hoped the talk of fiends here\nwas overstated, but this place is\noverflowing with them...
Ugh! There's no end to them!
They've got numbers, but that's all.\nStay calm. We'll be through 'em in—
Seems we're in a bit of a pickle here...
I will lend you my blade!
Her precision is astonishing...\nEvery swing is a mortal blow!
...That was the last of them.\nAre any of you hurt?
We're fine, thanks to you.\nMay I ask your name?
Celliera! I serve as knight's armsmaster.
Teachin' the sword to highborn children?\nThat's a pretty high-rankin' position.
Why have you come here? This mountain\nis no place for leisure hiking.
The villagers at the base asked our help\nin slaying fiends.
Aid to the people! A noble cause indeed.
And what brings you up here, Celliera?
A training camp—the rigors here are\nperfect for hardening both body and mind.
This a trainin' camp for one or somethin'?\nI don't see anybody with ya.
I WAS here with my students...until they\nfled for the foothills.
That giant fiend had them running scared.
Just how big a fiend was it?
It appeared before us out of nowhere,\nthen vanished like smoke and oakum.
Next thing I heard was a chorus of screams\nand a stampede of footsteps down the\nmountainside.
These rich whelps have no spleen at all!
And now yer stranded up here alone, yeah?
I do not fancy the implication, sir!\nI remained here quite intentionally.
I've no mind to leave this mountain until\nthe giant fiend is slain.
You're going to hunt it? Why?
As a lesson to the young ones! I'll toss\nthe corpse at their feet and lecture the\ndaylights out of the little cowards.
＂You turned tail and ran, from THIS?＂ Hah!\n...They'll soon learn there's no terror more\ndire than disappointing me.
It seems our aims align. Will you join us?
It makes sense. We're trying to clear out\nevery fiend here—including yours.
And if we hunt the same prey—
Then it only makes sense to do it together.\nIndeed, indeed.
Very well. I accept your offer.
Now, allow me to make you one in return!\n*grope*
Gah! What are you doing, and why does\nit involve so much touching?!
Hmm, I see. You've considerable tone,\nbut your muscles favor your dominant\nhand and pivot leg.
Wait, you can tell all that by touching me?
Muscles are loquacious things if you know\nhow to listen. Now, if you'll excuse me...
Mmm-hmm, mmmm-hm. Yes, well, I've a\nfirm grasp of all of your conditions now.\n...No pun intended.
A thought struck me as I watched you\ndispatch those fiends.
You're uncommon talents, to the last.\nDiamonds in the rough, just begging to\nbe dug out and polished!
My heart has been racing ever since!
I want to shape you. To put chisel to\nmarble and sculpt you into warriors fit\nto make history!
Well, you're certainly enthusiastic.\nDo you speak to all your students like this?
Please, you must allow me to train you for\nas long as we travel together. I insist!
Say the word, and I'll put together a\nregimen guaranteed to produce results\nin the brief time we share.
I'll stake my reputation as knight's\narmsmaster on this fact: You will leave\nthis mountain feeling stronger than ever!
And now that I'm acquainted with your\nmuscles, I can offer each of you my own\npersonalized advice.
It IS, isn't it? So then, say you will.\nPlease? Please please pleeeease?!
Her eyes have gone from sparkling to\nmadwoman, {player_name}.
If it can make us stronger, I see no reason\nto decline.
From this moment on, I am your knight's\narmsmaster! Is that understood?!
Ahh, I do love that sound. May I, uh...\nMay I have another round?
GOOD. All right then, listen up!
I'm going to make it my personal\nresponsibility to turn every last one\nof you little whelps into a WOLF!
First, let's get you warmed up—I want you\nto run to the peak and slay any fiends we\nfind along the way.
Hear what? And before you answer: no.\nYou sure it wasn't your imagination?
Stow the chatter, whelps! I'll kick any\nstragglers up this hill and back!
